House Resolution 795
By: Representative Jackson of the 128th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Lewis Grant; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Atlanta native Lewis Grant began his musical studies at the age of ten and by
3 age twelve began his professional career in entertainment with the vocal group "The
4 Continentals"; and
5 WHEREAS, after playing in the high school band, Lewis went on to study classical styles
6 of music at Clark College, now Clark Atlanta University, where he skillfully led the French
7 Horn section and sang first tenor in the Philharmonic Society; and
8 WHEREAS, with the awareness of what was needed on the contemporary sound scene,
9 Lewis started "The Prime Ministers Band," a music group that projected charisma, style,
10 versatility, and universal appeal; and
11 WHEREAS, "The Prime Ministers Band" became the house band for New York Mets, Don
12 Clendenon's Club, The Mine Shaft in Underground Atlanta, and the famous Paschal's La
13 Carrousel; and
